Author:  NEWTON
Vol / Page:  193
Edition:  1950
Quote:  <i>Barebelly</i>: A sheep which has lost the wool off its belly, i.e., torn off in matagouri or scrub. A sheep which has lost most of its wool is known as a `rosella.'
